<paragraph id="991B9A143548FFE8FF0C881C54DCD27F" blockId="6.[166,1225,962,1342]" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">
Remarks. It is believed that the melon fruit fly is now widespread in all the areas of melon plantings within 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843548FFE8FE3888FC5757D3DF" box="[495,594,1155,1182]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, as it was entirely neglected at the beginning of its spread. Furthermore, it has been found to be imported into many other regions of 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843548FFE8FBBF88DC51CDD3FF" box="[1128,1224,1187,1214]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
with melonstransported for commercial purposes; for instance, in the Transcarpatian Region (http://izan.kiev.ua/ukrbin/show_image.php?imageid = 41666). Its establishment, however, has been restricted to the southern 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843548FFE8FD16897C5621D25F" box="[705,804,1283,1310]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="459">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, which is the only appropriate area for cultivation of its hosts.
</paragraph>
